flowchart TD
  A[Trigger: New or updated Control Plan / FMEA / Process Flow or PPAP submission detected for a configured part or program.]
  A --> N1[Stream: DDM/Crawlers - Ingest APQP artifacts and PPAP packages from PLM, supplier portal, and SAP into the data foundation.]
  N1 --> N2[Stream: STREAMS - Normalize, validate metadata and perform completeness & BOM alignment checks.]
  N2 --> N3{PB: Agent Team - Agent synthesizes inputs, recommends control approaches and a validation plan, and proposes approval path.}
  N3 -->|Primary| N4[PB: CWB Lifecycle - Route recommendation through CWB for human review/accept/reject/override and capture decision rationale.]
  N4 --> N5[PB: Remote Functions - On approval, trigger PPAP request/supplier notification and SAP S/4HANA writebacks for part release or change via Remote Functions.]
  N5 --> N6[PB: UI Screen - Surface gateframe status, cycle-time KPIs, non-conformance trends and COGS impact to program teams and quality leads.]
  N6 --> Z1[Outcome: Shorter approval cycles with measurable reduction in rework and non-conformances, faster PPAP turnarounds, improved supplier collaboration, and downstream COGS and working-capital improvements from fewer holds and accelerated part releases.]
  N3 -->|Agent recommendation accepted by revi...| B1[Proceed with PPAP issuance and SAP writeback for part release.]
  B1 --> O1[Outcome: Standard approval path completed; reduced cycle time and on-time part release.]
  O1 --> End[End]
  N3 -->|Reviewers request supplier rework or ...| B2[Create task with required rework steps, route to supplier via CWB, and set gated rechecks; re-ingest updated artifacts.]
  B2 --> O2[Outcome: Controlled rework loop with traceability; increased short term cycle time but reduced downstream non-conformance risk.]
  O2 --> End[End]
  N3 -->|Supplier PPAP fails or supplier capab...| B3[Escalate to engineering and procurement via Process Builder, initiate deviation or containment workflow, and flag parts in SAP for hold.]
  B3 --> O3[Outcome: Rapid containment and corrective action routing to protect production and manage COGS impact.]
  O3 --> End[End]
  Z1 --> End[End]